# BRAIN.md — Your Vault Compass

> This file tells `brain` how YOU think about YOUR vault. It's read on every
> ingest, chat, brainstorm, and draft. Edit it freely — the LLM will adapt.
>
> This file is not a strict schema. It's a living instruction set written in
> plain English. The more specific you are, the more consistent the wiki
> will feel over time.

## Taxonomy

Describe the top-level topics or domains you care about. Examples:

- **research** — academic papers, technical deep dives, reading notes
- **work** — meeting notes, project updates, client context
- **personal** — journal, family, health (kept private by default)

For each domain, note what kinds of sources belong in it and any naming
conventions you want followed.

## Naming Conventions

- Note filenames use `kebab-case.md` (e.g. `attention-is-all-you-need.md`).
- Wiki notes live under `<domain>/notes/` by default.
- Source notes (one per ingested artifact) live under `<domain>/sources/`.
- Indexes live at `<domain>/index.md`.

Override any of these here if you prefer a different layout.

## Wikilink Rules

- Prefer `[[note-stem]]` over `[[Full Title]]` when the stem is unambiguous.
- New wiki notes should link to at least one existing note if semantically related.
- The integrate step (LLM) will propose new wikilinks; you can reject them in the
  approval queue.

